<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>86<percent/> of 35</li> 
<li>31<percent/> of 198</li> 
<li>1<percent/> of 1630</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 31<percent/> of 198</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{86}\%\cdot{35}={30.1}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{31}\%\cdot{198}={61.38}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1}\%\cdot{1630}={16.3}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 31<percent/> of 198 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
